The '''conditional change model''' in [[statistics]] is the analytic procedure in which change scores are [[linear regression|regressed]] on [[:wikt:baseline|baseline]] values, together with the [[explanatory variable]]s of interest (often including indicators of [[treatment groups]]).  The method has some substantial advantages over the usual [[two-sample t-test]] recommended in [[textbook]]s.

